In a meeting between President Biden and President Lasso of Ecuador, the two leaders discussed deepening security and economic partnerships. They also talked about joint investment programs addressing security needs in Ecuador's prison system, justice sector, and maritime security. President Biden thanked President Lasso for his moral leadership and condemnation of Putin's war against Ukraine. They expressed their shared vision of a free and democratic future and pledged to work together on the United Nations Security Council. President Lasso reaffirmed Ecuador's commitment to democracy, peace, and justice, and their support for dialogue and multilateralism. The leaders emphasized the importance of their alliance and discussed expanding and strengthening their relationship.